<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-085-682  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 085 682.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Jan 22 1990 v36 n1793 p24(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Motorola describes 68040 MPU. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zipper, Stuart.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Reduced instruction-set computer (RISC) features and an on-chipfloating point unit have been incorporated into Motorola Inc's68040 MPU, 25 MHz processor.andP;  The RISC-like center on theoptimization of most frequently used instructions and addressingmodes for single cycle execution by the integer unit.andP;  The circuitprocess averages an instruction every 1.3 clock cycles, and issoftware compatible with all earlier members of the 68000 family.andO;Data and instruction caches, two memory management units, theinteger unit as well as the floating point unit are all integratedinto the 040.andP;  The processor is currently priced at $795, and ispackaged in a 179-pin ceramic grid array, and is available now.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MOT.andO;Product:   Motorola 68040 (Microprocessor) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Processor SpeedProduct IntroductionMicroprocessorsReduced instruction set computersComplementary Metal Oxide Semiconductors.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>